Simple Calculator
A clean, modern calculator application built with Python and Tkinter. This calculator supports basic arithmetic operations with a sleek dark theme interface.

Features
Basic arithmetic operations (+, -, ×, ÷)

Percentage calculations

Decimal point operations

Positive/negative toggle

Keyboard support

Clean dark theme interface

Error handling for edge cases

Installation
Make sure you have Python 3.6 or higher installed

Tkinter should come with standard Python installations

How to Run
Save the code as calculator.py

Open terminal/command prompt

Navigate to the file location:

bash
cd path/to/folder
Run the program:

bash
python calculator.py
or

bash
python3 calculator.py
Usage
Click buttons with mouse or use keyboard

Use 'C' to clear everything

Use '⌫' to delete last digit

Use '+/-' to toggle positive/negative

Use '%' for percentage calculations

Keyboard Shortcuts
Numbers: 0-9

Operators: +, -, *, /

Decimal: .

Equals: Enter or =

Clear: Escape or Delete

Backspace: Backspace

Troubleshooting
If you get "Python is not recognized":

Install Python from python.org

Check "Add Python to PATH" during installation

Restart terminal after installation

If you get "No module named 'tkinter'":

Linux: sudo apt-get install python3-tk (Ubuntu/Debian)

Project Structure
calculator.py - Main application file

